{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778550218,"nonce":"rG20n00RzDVPuaf+144hRRDj3vM=","message":"**Worktree artifact loss** — rlrmp issue `0887e3e`\n\nGitignored artifacts (`_artifacts/`) generated in a feature worktree are silently deleted when `dwt` cleans up the worktree after auth merge. Root cause: `rlrmp/paths.py::REPO_ROOT` and `feedbax/plot/io.py::_find_repo_root` both derive the repo root from `__file__`, pointing at the worktree directory instead of the main repo root.\n\nRecommended fix: add `_artifacts` to `rlrmp/.worktree.yaml` `shared:` list — worktrees symlink to main repo's `_artifacts/` at creation time via existing `wt` infrastructure. Rlrmp-only change, no dotfiles/mandible/feedbax changes required for the recommended approach.\n\nOptional deeper fix (out of scope for now): update `feedbax/plot/io.py::_find_repo_root` to detect worktree context (`.git` file vs directory) and return the main worktree root. Would be a feedbax-side change.","files":null}]}